    ‚àá
    ‚àá (names parents scriptitems)‚ÜêGetFileTiesIn rootns;all;allrefs;mask;parents;r;t;urefs
     ‚çù Find all file system links to objects below rootns
      allrefs‚Üê2‚äÉ¬®all‚Üê5177‚å∂‚ç¨
      t‚Üêurefs‚Üê‚à™allrefs
      mask‚Üê(‚â¢urefs)‚ç¥0
      :If 0‚âÝ‚â¢t ‚ãÑ :Repeat
              mask‚à®‚Üê(‚çï¬®t)‚àä(‚äÇ‚çïrootns) ‚çù Have we reached rootns?  - ‚çï because of mantis 18147
              :If t‚â°t.## ‚ãÑ :Leave ‚ãÑ :EndIf  ‚çù continue until everything is root
              t‚Üêt.##         ‚çù Move all pointers up to parent
          :EndRepeat ‚ãÑ :EndIf
      :If 0=‚â¢r‚Üê(allrefs‚àämask/urefs)/all ‚çù selection of 5177‚å∂‚ç¨
          names‚Üê0‚ç¥‚äÇ'' ‚ãÑ parents‚Üê0‚ç¥# ‚ãÑ scriptitems‚Üê‚ç¨
      :Else
          names‚Üê‚çï¬®1‚äÉ¬®r
          parents‚Üê‚çé¬®‚çï¬®2‚äÉ¬®r ‚çù need ‚çé¬®‚çï¬® because of mantis 18147
          scriptitems‚ÜêIsScripted EachUnique parents  ‚çù parent is scripted ‚Üí item is a script item
      :EndIf
    ‚àá
    ‚àá r‚ÜêRemoveFileTiesIn rootns;names;parents;scriptitems
     ‚çù Find all file system links to objects below rootns, and remove using 5178‚å∂
     ‚çù Return number of links broken
      (names parents scriptitems)‚ÜêGetFileTiesIn rootns ‚çù links to be removed
      ‚çù there might be some orphaned script items - interpreter must forget about them
      ‚çù do it first because of mantis 18606
      :If 1‚àäscriptitems ‚çù script items are simply untied
          {}(scriptitems/parents){‚ç∫.(5178‚å∂)‚çµ}¬®(scriptitems/names)
      :EndIf
      :If 0‚àäscriptitems  ‚çù scripts are more complicated because of Mantis 18148
          r‚Üê+/((~scriptitems)/parents)Untie¬®((~scriptitems)/names)
      :Else
          r‚Üê0
      :EndIf
    ‚àá

    ‚àá changed‚ÜêFileHasChanged(ns name file filesrc);compsrc;file2;hash;line;lines;name2;nameref;nc;parent;ts;nc2;aplsrc
      compsrc‚Üê0 ‚ãÑ changed‚Üê0
      (name2 parent nc2 file2 line lines hash ts)‚Üêns.(5179‚å∂)name  ‚çù name2 may be a name or a ref - parent is a ref
      :If 0=nc‚Üêns NameClass name ‚ãÑ changed‚Üê1  ‚çù name not defined - need to update from file
      :ElseIf 0‚àä‚ç¥name2 ‚ãÑ compsrc‚Üê1 ‚çù not tied at all - need to compare sources directly
      :ElseIf file‚â¢file2 ‚ãÑ changed‚Üê1  ‚çù not the same file
      :ElseIf hash‚â¢FileHash file ‚ãÑ changed‚Üê1 ‚çù not the same hash - unfortunately, there could be a false negative with CRC32 - e.g. swap two bytes that are offset by 4 bytes : '‚åà,‚åä'‚Üí'‚åä,‚åà' or 'A,B,C'‚Üí'C,B,A'
      :EndIf
      :If compsrc ‚ãÑ ‚çù need a closer look
          :If 0‚àä‚ç¥filesrc ‚ãÑ filesrc‚ÜêGetFileSource file ‚ãÑ :EndIf
          aplsrc‚Üêns GetAplSource name
          changed‚Üê~CompareSource aplsrc filesrc nc nc2  ‚çù compare source to be sure - will return 1 where whitespace not preserved
      :EndIf
    ‚àá

    ‚àá r‚ÜêViewMetaData mode
    ‚çù Experiemental function to inspect Link meta data.
    ‚çù For debugging only.
    ‚çù !!! DO NOT USE THIS function in application code!!!
      r‚Üê5177‚å∂‚ç¨
      r‚Üê(~(8‚Üë¬®‚çï¬®2‚äÉ¬®r)‚àä‚äÇ'‚éïSE.Link')/r
      r‚Üêr[‚çã‚çï‚åΩ‚Üë2‚Üë¬®r]
     
      :Select mode
      :Case 'raw' ‚ãÑ ‚Üí0
      :Case 'count' ‚ãÑ r‚Üê(‚çï¬®2‚äÉ¬®r){‚ç∫(‚â¢‚çµ)}‚å∏1‚äÉ¬®r
      :Case 'group' ‚ãÑ r‚Üê(‚çï¬®2‚äÉ¬®r){‚ç∫ ‚çµ}‚å∏1‚äÉ¬®r
      :CaseList '' 'report'
          r‚Üê‚Üë4‚Üë¬®r
          r[;1]‚Üê(‚çï¬®r[;2]),¬®'.',¬®r[;1]
          r‚Üêr[;1 3 4]
      :Else
          'mode must be one of: raw count group report'‚éïSIGNAL 11
      :EndSelect
