    ‚àá name‚ÜêCaseCodePart name;bin;digits;len;‚éïIO
    ‚çù case-code a string
      ‚éïIO‚Üê0
      ‚Üí0 If 0=‚â¢name  ‚çù empty name doesn't get case coded
      bin‚Üêname‚âÝ0 CaseText name
      len‚Üê‚åà3√∑‚ç®‚â¢bin
      digits‚Üê2‚ä•‚åΩ‚çâ‚åΩlen 3‚ç¥bin‚Üë‚ç®3√ólen
      digits‚Üì‚ç®‚Üê+/‚àß\0=digits
      name,‚Üê'-',‚éïD[digits,0/‚ç®‚ç¨‚â°digits]
    ‚àá
    ‚àá name‚ÜêStripCaseCodePart name;code;length;mask;‚éïIO
    ‚çù strip case code from a string
      ‚éïIO‚Üê0
      length‚Üê(‚åΩname)‚ç≥'-'
      ‚Üí0 If length‚àä0,‚â¢name   ‚çù case code must be after hyphen
      code‚Üê‚éïD‚ç≥(-length)‚Üëname
      name‚Üê((-length+1)‚Üìname)
      ‚Üí0 If code‚à®.>7         ‚çù case code must be octal digits
      ‚Üí0 If(‚åà3√∑‚ç®‚â¢name)‚âÝ(‚â¢code)  ‚çù case code must be of correct length
      mask‚Üê‚åΩ,‚çâ2 2 2‚ä§code     ‚çù boolean mask of upper-case
      ‚Üí0 If~(‚äÇ(‚â¢name)‚Üìmask)‚àä‚ç¨(,0)(0 0)  ‚çù mask must be padded with 0-2 zeros
      name‚Üê((‚â¢name)‚Üëmask)CaseText¬®name
    ‚àá
    ‚àá name‚Üê(dir CaseCode flatten)name;ext;file;parts;path
    ‚çù case-code a file located under linked dir
      :If name‚â°dir ‚ãÑ :Return ‚ãÑ :EndIf  ‚çù would wrongfully cut name because of missing trailing slash
      (path file ext)‚Üê1 ‚éïNPARTS name
      :If flatten  ‚çù case code file name only
          file‚ÜêCaseCodePart file
          name‚Üê‚àäpath file ext
      :Else  ‚çù case code sub-directories too
          path‚Üê(‚â¢dir)‚Üìpath       ‚çù do not case-code linked directory
          parts‚Üê(Parts path),‚äÇfile
          parts‚ÜêCaseCodePart¬®parts      ‚çù case-code each part of path independently
          name‚Üê'/'JoinList(‚äÇdir),parts
          name,‚Üêext
      :EndIf
    ‚àá
    ‚àá name‚Üê(dir StripCaseCode flatten)name;ext;file;parts;path
    ‚çù strip case code from a file name located under linked dir
      :If ~'-'‚àä(‚â¢dir)‚Üìname  ‚çù no casecode
      :OrIf name‚â°dir  ‚çù would wrongfully cut name because of missing trailing slash
          :Return
      :EndIf
      (path file ext)‚Üê1 ‚éïNPARTS name
      :If flatten   ‚çù only file name is case coded
          file‚ÜêStripCaseCodePart file
          name‚Üê‚àäpath file ext
      :Else  ‚çù sub-directories are case-coded
          path‚Üê(‚â¢dir)‚Üìpath       ‚çù do not case-code linked directory
          parts‚Üê(Parts path),‚äÇfile
          parts‚ÜêStripCaseCodePart¬®parts      ‚çù case-code each part of path independently
          name‚Üê'/'JoinList(‚äÇdir),parts
          name,‚Üêext
      :EndIf
